An official proposal that Finlandscrap price controls and replace them with a system aimed atpromoting competition is expected to go to parliament laterthis year, officials said.    The proposal handed to the government yesterday calls forparliament to be empowered to order three-month price freezesin place of the controls.    It proposes that a new board be set up to ensure largefirms do not abuse their market positions and that monopoliesdo not expand beyond their approved sectors. REUTER&#3;